Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Soak your @bamboo skewers{6} in cold water (this will prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve and peel the @red onion{}(1, halved and peeled), then cut each half into 4 wedges.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @British chicken breasts{2}(diced) and @curry powder mix{1%sachet}. Toss to coat in the spices.

Add the onion wedges, @korma curry paste{50%g} and a third of the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat well.

Carefully thread the chicken and onion wedges onto the skewers (3 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Transfer the skewers to a lightly oiled large baking tray. Spoon over any remaining korma yoghurt from the bowl.

Bake the skewers on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @iceberg lettuce{1/2}(trimmed and sliced thinly), halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and coarsely grated), then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

In a medium bowl, combine the remaining Greek style yoghurt, half the lemon juice and a pinch of @salt{} and @sugar{}.

When the skewers have ~{5%minutes} remaining, drizzle over the @honey{2%tbsp}. Turn to coat and bake for the remaining time.

Just before serving, add the lettuce and carrot to the yoghurt dressing. Toss to coat.

Share the korma chicken skewers between your plates. Spoon over any remaining sauce from the tray.

Serve the chips, carrot salad and remaining lemon wedges alongside.

Add a dollop of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping. Enjoy!